Title:
trustme — BOF to impersonate TrustedInstaller via DISM API trigger and thread impersonation

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
`trustme` is a Cobalt Strike Beacon Object File (BOF) that elevates an already-admin Beacon to a token that includes the `NT SERVICE\TrustedInstaller` group, enabling modification of TrustedInstaller-owned resources (files/registry) that SYSTEM alone may not access. Instead of starting the TrustedInstaller service via the Service Control Manager (a commonly monitored/logged path), it triggers `TrustedInstaller.exe` indirectly by loading `dismapi.dll` and running a DISM health check (`DismCheckImageHealth`) while keeping the DISM session open. It enumerates processes and threads using native NT APIs (`NtGetNextProcess`/`NtGetNextThread`) and identifies TrustedInstaller by querying process image names (`NtQueryInformationProcess`). It then impersonates a TrustedInstaller thread using `NtImpersonateThread` and applies the resulting token to the Beacon session via `BeaconUseToken` until `rev2self`. This is primarily useful for red teams/pentesters operating post-exploitation on Windows who need TrustedInstaller-level access with reduced SCM telemetry.

Technical Focus:
- TrustedInstaller token/group impersonation
- DISM API abuse to spawn TrustedInstaller (`dismapi.dll`, `DismCheckImageHealth`)
- Native NT process/thread enumeration (`NtGetNextProcess`, `NtGetNextThread`)
- Thread impersonation (`NtImpersonateThread`) and token handling in Beacon (`BeaconUseToken`)
- Privilege requirements and enablement (`SeDebugPrivilege`)
- Evasion/telemetry reduction by avoiding SCM interactions

Use Cases:
- Modify/replace TrustedInstaller-protected system binaries and components
- Write to protected registry hives/keys owned by TrustedInstaller
- Post-exploitation privilege escalation from admin to TrustedInstaller-equivalent access
- Red-team tradecraft to avoid direct `sc start TrustedInstaller` / `StartServiceW` artifacts
- Operationalizing TrustedInstaller impersonation as a Cobalt Strike BOF + CNA command

Keywords:
Cobalt Strike, BOF, Beacon, TrustedInstaller, NT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller, SYSTEM, token impersonation, thread impersonation, NtImpersonateThread, NtGetNextProcess, NtGetNextThread, NtQueryInformationProcess, ProcessImageFileName, DISM, dismapi.dll, DismCheckImageHealth, SeDebugPrivilege, Windows internals, SCM evasion, rev2self